frameDefinitions: An Agent changes the filler of a  Role by placing a New filler in the position after the Old filler ceases to occupy the position.
An organic item, the Patient, has undergone the natural process of rotting  and decaying with a possible expression of the Degree to which the rotting has occurred.
Some individual or group ceases to be able to sustain an Endeavor (a long-term activity involving economic interaction with the public, often a business venture).
Unless a particular Required_situation obtains, Negative_consequences will follow.

An Initial_element is converted into a Final_element via a process of decay, fusion, or fission which changes the number or type of hadrons (protons or neutrons) in the nucleus of the atoms that make up the Element.  '5.5 percent of nucleii decay from tritium to He3 in a year .'
In this frame a Patient is in a phase brought about after a change of phase.
frameExamples: If you <t>replace</t> me with a robot, who's gonna make excuses to your wife for you?
You <t>must</t> turn in your test by 5 p.m.
5.5 percent of nucleii <t>decay</t> from tritium to He3 in a year .
Collect up the  <t>thawed</t> water from the freezer section.
listRoleDefinitions: The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs actions resulting in the <fen>New</fen> entity occupying the position.
The <fen>New</fen> entity is the person or thing that the <fen>Agent</fen> sets to fill a <fen>Role</fen>.
The entity that formerly occupied the position.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the New entity.
This role identifies where the <fen>Agent</fen> installs the <fen>New</fen> entity.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the organic matter that has decayed.
The <fen>Endeavor</fen> is rendered unable to continue its regular operations.
The period during which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is necessary to prevent negative consequences.
The location within which the <fen>Required_situation</fen> is required.
A substance definable in terms of the kind(s) of atoms that make it up.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that results from the process.
The type of <fen>Element</fen> that begins the process.
The time at which the <fen>Element</fen> undergoes the transformation.
The location where the nuclear process occurs.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is the entity which has had its phase altered.
